resolution: "Added --body-file <path> to pm create and pm update via new src/core/io/body-file.ts resolveBodyFileContent helper (CLI-only input alias, mutually exclusive with --body, actionable errors for conflict/empty-path/unreadable). Wired into create+update actions before normalize, CREATE/UPDATE_FLAG_CONTRACTS + zsh/fish completion + contracts golden + docs. 100% unit-covered + in-process integration tests."
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-13T20:59:26.222Z",claude-code-agent,"Plan: new core helper src/core/io/body-file.ts resolveBodyFileContent(bodyFile, body, readFileImpl?) — reads file (utf8), errors if --body also set (mutually exclusive) or path missing/unreadable. Register --body-file <path> commander option on create+update (direct .option) + add to CREATE_FLAG_CONTRACTS/UPDATE_FLAG_CONTRACTS for completion. Resolve+delete in create/update actions before normalize. CLI-only (no MCP — file paths meaningless over MCP, like history --diff). Mutual-exclusion error mirrors existing guided-error shape."
close_reason: "Added --body-file <path> to pm create and pm update via new src/core/io/body-file.ts resolveBodyFileContent helper (CLI-only input alias, mutually exclusive with --body, actionable errors for conflict/empty-path/unreadable). Wired into create+update actions before normalize, CREATE/UPDATE_FLAG_CONTRACTS + zsh/fish completion + contracts golden + docs. 100% unit-covered + in-process integration tests."
body: "Add --body-file <path> to pm create and pm update so agents can supply long markdown bodies (multi-paragraph, code blocks, tables) from a file instead of escaping huge inline --body strings or doing a second pm append call. Mutually exclusive with inline --body. '-' reads from stdin. Reduces round-trips (project management = context management)."
